Group-

I'm finally removing my fuel tank for general clean-up, and want to hear from someone who's done it before.  My bus is a '71, and the good news is that the engine is out (I'm still in restoration mode).  I have the cover plate off (i.e. the metal sheet which hides/closes the tank.  I've even got the two straps that secure the tank removed.

So what's next?

I'm "sure" that there's still gas in the tank.  Should I siphon it out from the side of the bus (i.e. filler cap)?  Maybe there's an easy way to drain the tank before loosing all the hoses and pullin' real hard to get 'er out?

Timely responses are welcome, as I'm trying to do this tonight.

